b'The laughter, the tears, and all of the beautiful ridiculousness that we went through will remain with me, always.\nPhoto: Herman Leonard'
b'He was the sweetest most sensitive man you could ever meet and had a passion for music and art that burned until his final breath. We were family and I was blessed to have him in my life.'

b'He had an extensive list of people that he worked with, live and in the studio, from The Rolling Stones to The Isley Brothers. In the studio he recorded my Black and White America and Strut albums.'

b'was the King of Pop,he\xe2\x80\x99d said it all.\r\rMay you rest in peace sweet Michael. You gave us all you had to give. Lenny.'
b'what I\xe2\x80\x99m\rdoing. He gave me joy as a child and showed me the way to go. He was music. Period. His hugeness as a star was great but before he'
b'He was the first live performer I ever saw. I got to see him at Madison\rSquare Garden when I was eight. If not for him, I wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t be doing'
b'I also saw what a beautiful father he was. He\rwas a beautiful human being. I am deeply saddened this evening.'
b'not been released and it was\rthe most amazing experience I\xe2\x80\x99ve had in the studio. He was funny. Very funny\rand we laughed the whole time.'
b'Even if he had not done Off the Wall or\rThriller, he would still be a genius in my eyes.\rI got to work with Michael  on a track that has'
b'he was a great singer but\rdidn\xe2\x80\x99t have feeling like James Brown. That somebody is not listening\rcarefully. As a child he did it all.'
b'That line between child and experienced adult took his\rexpression to an unmatched level.\r\rI heard somebody on the BBC news tonight say that'
b'Aretha Franklin. But the thing he had that\rthey could not match was the fact that he was a child. But at the same time\rhe sang as an adult.'
b'and listen to that voice. The\rpurity, the feeling, the interpretation of the lyrics. At the age of ten, he\rwas on par with James Brown and'
b'But the truth of the matter is he\rwas a boy that God blessed with the most angelic voice. Just listen to an early Jackson Five album'
b'How Thriller was the biggest selling album in history. They speak about the controversy and countless other things.'
b'There will never be another talent like Michael Jackson. Many people are saying what a performer, what an icon. How many Grammy\xe2\x80\x99s he won.'
